view at high command, a junior officer’s experience at the platoon level, and the vantage points of many lesser-known Canadian soldiers who made the ultimate sacrifice. This innovative graphic history invites readers to reimagine the First World War through the eyes of those who lived it and to think more deeply about how we visualize and remember the past.Combining outstanding original art and thought-provoking commentary, Through Their Eyes uncovers the fascinating stories behind this battle while creatively expanding the ways that history is shared and represented.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHill 70, Battle of, France, 1917vComic books, strips, etc. 0aLens, Battle of, Lens, France, 1917vComic books, strips, etc. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xCampaignszFrancevComic books, strips, etc. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xRegimental historieszCanadavComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / History.2bisacsh  aAY Jackson.  aArthur Currie.  aBrock Chisholm.  aCanadian Expeditionary Force.  aDouglas Haig.  aFrance.  aGermany.  aGreat War.  aLens.  aLittle Nemo.  aPasschendaele.  aSecond Ypres.  aVictoria Cross.  aVimy Ridge.  aWW1.  aWestern Front.  aWilliam Rider Rider.  aWorld War 1.  aarmy.  aartillery.  aassault.  abattalion.  abattle.  abattlefield.  abrigade.  aburial.  acaricature.  acartoon.  acomics.  acommemoration.  adeath.  agraphic novel.  ahistoriography.  ahonour.  aillustrated.  aimagination.  ainfantry.  amaps.  amilitary history.  aphotography.  apictures.  arepresentation.  asacrifice.  ashell.  atrenches.  avisualize.  awar art.  awar graves.1 aEngen, Robert C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801248140uhttps://www.degr